What's New in JDK 8
 
Java Platform, Standard Edition 8 is a major feature release.

Java Programming Language

Lambda Expressions
treat functionality as a method argument, or code as data
expressed via instances of single-method interfaces 
called functional interfaces
Method references
easy-to-read lambda expressions for methods that already have
a name
Default methods
enable new functionality to be added to the interfaces
ensure binary compatibility with code written for older versions of those interfaces
Repeating Annotations
ability to apply the same annotation type more than
once to the same declaration or type use
Type Annotations 
ability to apply an annotation anywhere a type is used
Improved type inference.

Method parameter reflection.



Collections
new java.util.stream package.
provide a Stream API to support functional-style operations on streams of elements
The Stream API is integrated into the Collections API
allowing bulk operations on collections, 
sequential or parallel map-reduce transformations


Compact Profiles
new Compact Profiles.
Compact Profiles contain predefined subsets of the Java SE platform and enable applications that do not require the entire Platform to be deployed and run on small devices.














































